    <note>Huang(2) Deli [15448] For kinship relationship with Huang(2) Shi(2) [3418], see documentation for son, Cishan [15449]. Great great grandson notes ancestry to Jinhua (i.e. Dongyang) and migration to Hong, Fengcheng. Therefore, segementation between this branch of the Hongzhou Huang and that of Huang(2) Tingjian [7111] et al. took place at an early date. According to Zhou Bida's funerary inscription for Deli's grandson, Muzhi [15455], the family was a great surname (zhuxing) of Yuzhang, Deli established his family branch of the lineage (qijia) through earning the jinshi and three of his six sons earned the degree. Nanchang FZ, 39.5a. CBD, 4, 2913.</note>
